section.section:
In accordance with the procedure set forth in this subtitle, the appropriate district council may require the Commission to prepare the general plan, or any amendment to the plan, considering elements such as:
existing and forecasted:
population, including population distribution and other appropriate characteristics;
amount, type, intensity, general location, and characteristics of commercial, industrial, and public sector facilities and related employment;
amount, type, need, and location of major public services, facilities, and utilities;
transportation needs, facilities, routes, and systems; and
housing demand and needs, and the amount, type, quality, and general location of housing;
existing land uses, forecasts of land absorption rates or markets, and analyses of the amount, general location, and interrelationships among different categories of land use;
staging or scheduling of development and capital improvements, and the fiscal or economic impact of those improvements;
physical resources and conditions, including topography, soils, geology and mineral deposits, hydrology and waterways, wetlands and shorelines, water and air quality, climate, noise, open spaces, scenic areas, vegetation, forests, agricultural lands, fisheries, wildlife and wildlife habitats, and other areas of environmental or ecological importance or sensitivity;
sites, structures, areas, or settings of archaeological, historical, architectural, cultural, or scenic value or significance;
extent and general location of physically blighted or deteriorated areas and related factors;
evaluation of the probable consequences of major recommendations of the general plan on the general physical and social environment and population of the regional district;
estimates of the probable consequences on public revenues and expenditures of major recommendations of the general plan; and
any other matter that the appropriate district council or the Commission determines to be necessary and feasible to the preparation or presentation of the general plan.

The materials in paragraphs (1) and (2) of this subsection are guidelines for the basis, content, and consideration of:
the general plan;
a functional master plan;
an area master plan; or
any amendment to the plans.
